  "prompt": "Why do birth control pills contain acetaminophen?",
  "response": "Birth control pills do not contain acetaminophen. Birth control pills primarily contain hormones such as estrogen and progestin, which work to prevent pregnancy by stopping ovulation, thickening cervical mucus, and thinning the lining of the uterus. Acetaminophen, on the other hand, is a pain reliever and fever reducer commonly found in over-the-counter medications like Tylenol. If you have any concerns about the ingredients in your birth control or any other medication, it's best to consult with a healthcare provider.",
